<chapter id="clsJson">
<title>json Class</title>
<para>
The <classname>json</classname> class allows to create and process <emphasis role="italic">JSON (JavaScript Object Notation)</emphasis> data. The
<emphasis role="italic">JSON</emphasis> definition used for this implementation can be found at
<ulink url="https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4627.txt">https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4627.txt</ulink>.
</para>
<note><para>
This implementation does not transform into or from Unicode escape sequences in the form of &quot;\uXXXX&quot;.
</para></note>

<para>To use <classname>json</classname> class, you must place the following directive
in your script:
<programlisting>
::requires json.cls
</programlisting>
</para>

